cs.CE, cs.NA, cs.MS, cs.DC, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper presents a software package for solving elastic problems using the Smoothed Finite Element Method (S-FEM), which is a numerical method commonly used in computational engineering and science. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper focuses on the implementation and evaluation of a numerical method, the S-FEM, for solving elastic problems. 
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software): The paper presents an open-source software package, juSFEM, for implementing the S-FEM method. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper discusses the parallel implementation of the S-FEM method using the Julia language on multi-core CPUs. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper discusses the design and implementation of an open-source software package, juSFEM, for the S-FEM method, which involves software engineering principles and practices.
